{
  "texts": [
    "This analytical approach empowers companies to respond effectively to emerging trends, allowing them to adjust formulations and marketing strategies based on insights derived from big data analysis.",
    "For example, understanding shifting consumer demands for healthier or more innovative products enables manufacturers to align their offerings with market expectations, thereby enhancing competitive advantage.",
    "The integration of AI and blockchain technologies is beginning to shape secure infrastructures for sensory data management (Hao et al. 2023a (Hao et al., 2023b)), particularly in olfactory and gustatory analysis.",
    "In such systems, electronic noses and tongues generate high-dimensional sensory data used to detect spoilage, contamination, or mislabeling in food products.",
    "AI models analyze these sensory signatures to identify irregularities, while blockchain functions as a decentralized ledger to securely record outputs along with metadata such as timestamps, locations, and batch identifiers."
  ]
}